      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De ira</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e112">De ira rixae, tumor mentis, contumeliae, clamor,
              indignatio, blasphemiae proferuntur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e127">Plerumque mentem, sub obtentu justitiae; irae
              immanitas vastat; et dum quasi saevit zelo rectitudinis, rabiem explet ira
              furoris.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e142">Qui humanorum actuum subtili examine gressus
              enumerat, iram sine voce, judicio; iram in voce, concilio; iram vero in voce atque
              sermone, gehennae ignibus mancipat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e157">Plus semper ira in vindicta exigit, quam de
              injuria accepit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in
              <title>Dialogis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e173">Tanto metuenda est ira justorum, quanto et
              constat quia in eorum cordibus ille praesens est, qui ad inferendam ultionem, quam
              voluerit, invalidus non est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in
              <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e188">Ira, etiam cum delinquentium culpas insequitur,
              non debet menti nostrae quasi domina praeire; sed post rationis tergum, quasi ancilla
              rationis, subnixius famulari.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e195">Gregorius, in
              <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e203">Nemo potest diligere illum, quem ex ira vel odio
              non vult videre.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e210">Gregorius, in
              <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e218">Ira si semel mentem possidere coeperit, justum
              esse deputat etiam illud, quod crudeliter facit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e225">Gregorius, in
              <title>Pastorali</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e233">Illa quae mater est omnium custosque virtutum,
              per irae vel impatientiae vitium virtus charitatis enervatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e240">Hieronymus, in
            originali <title>super Michaeam</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e248">Propemodum naturale est, ut et nurus socrum, et
              socrus oderit nurum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e256">Augustinus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e264">Sicut acetum corrumpit vas, si diutius ibi
              fuerit, sic ira corrumpit cor, si in alium diem duraverit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e271">Augustinus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e279">Multo melius nec juste cuiquam irascimur, quam
              velut juste irascendo, in alicujus odium irae occulta facilitate dilabimur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e284">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e294" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e286">Augustinus,
              <title>de Sermone Domini in monte</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e294">Si irasci non est fas fratri suo sine causa, aut
              dicere: <!--<i>-->Raca<!--</i>-->, aut dicere: <!--<i>-->Fatue<!--</i>-->, multo minus
              fas est animo tenere aliquid, ut in odium indignatio convertatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e307">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e317" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e309">Augustinus,
              <title>de Civitate Dei</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e317"
              source="http://scta.info/resource/adcd-l14-d1e2088">Iram nihil aliud esse, quam
              ulciscendi libidinem, veteres diffinierunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e322">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e332" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e324">Augustinus, in
              <title>Regula</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e332">Melior est, qui quamvis ira saepe tentatur,
              tamen impetrare festinat, ut sibi dimittat, cui se fecisse agnoscit injuriam, quam qui
              tardius irascitur, et ad veniam petendam tardius inclinatur. Qui autem nunquam petit
              veniam, aut non ex animo petit, sine causa est in monasterio, etiamsi inde non
              projiciatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e337">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e344" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e339">Glossa</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e344">Si non dimiserimus ex corde, quod in nos
              delinquitur, etiam hoc quod per poenitentiam dimissum erat, a nobis exigetur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e350">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e360" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e352">Cassiodorus, in
              <title>Psalmos</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e360">Venialis ira est, quae non ducitur ad
              effectum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e365">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e375" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e367">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>super Joannem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e375">Qui irascitur sine ratione, multis suppliciis
              dignus erit, voluntarie seipsum in barathra perditionis ferens, et ante futuram
              gehennam, hic jam vindictam solvens.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e380">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e390" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e382">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>de Compunctione cordis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e390">Non iracundos tantum et illatae malitiae memores
              punit Deus tanquam reos; sed et eos, qui et irascentes aut offensos fratres placare
              negligunt et contemnunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e395">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e405" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e397">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>de Compunctione cordis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e405">Osculum pacis porrigere tempore, quo sacramenta
              offeruntur, in usu Ecclesiae est. Sed vereor ne plures ex nobis labiis tantummodo
              pacem faciant, cum tamen Christus non ex ore, sed ex corde desideret, et affectu velit
              proximum, non labiis salutari.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e410">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e420" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e412">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>de Compunctione cordis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e420">Si tantummodo non laedas eum, qui te laesit,
              avertas autem te ab eo, nec libenter eum videas, manet sine dubio vulnus in pectore,
              et irae dolor augescit in corde.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e425">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e435" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e427">Ambrosius,
              <title>de Officiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e435">Si irascimur, quia affectus naturae est, non
              potestatis, malum sermonem non proferamus de ore nostro, ne in culpam ruamus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e441">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e451" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e443">Ambrosius,
              <title>de Officiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e451">Is qui cito injuria illata movetur, facit se
              dignum judicari contumelia, dum vult ea indignus haberi.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-d1e456">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e466" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Rd1e458">Bernardus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14912-Qd1e466">Non irasci, ubi irascendum sit, nolle emendare
              peccatum est; prius vero irasci, quam irascendum sit, peccatum peccato addere
              est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
